  "prompt": "How many people have a net worth of 20 million dollars?",
  "response": "The number of individuals with a net worth of at least $20 million varies depending on the source and methodology used to estimate wealth. As of recent data (2023), here are some key insights:\n\n1. **Credit Suisse Global Wealth Report (2022)**:\n   - The report estimated that there were approximately **2.7 million** individuals worldwide with a net worth of $50 million or more. This includes ultra-high-net-worth individuals (UHNWIs).\n   - Those with a net worth of $20 million or more would likely be a subset of this group.\n\n2. **Wealth-X and Knight Frank Reports**:\n   - Wealth-X and Knight Frank report similar figures, estimating that there are around **264,000** individuals globally with a net worth of $30 million or more.\n   - Those with $20 million or more would be a larger number, potentially in the range of **500,000 to 700,000** globally.\n\n3. **Regional Distribution**:\n   - The United States has the highest concentration of millionaires and multi-millionaires, followed by China and parts of Europe.\n   - Emerging markets, such as India and Southeast Asia, are also seeing growth in the number of high-net-worth individuals.\n\nThese numbers are approximate and can fluctuate due to economic conditions, asset valuations, and other factors. For the most accurate and up-to-date figures, reports from financial institutions like Credit Suisse, Wealth-X, or Knight Frank are the best sources.",
